How to run jupyter notebook from remote server Step1 : Start jupyter notebook in remote server
nohup jupyter notebook --no-browser --port=8889  Step2 : Connect from remote server
ssh -N -f -L localhost:8889:localhost:8890 remote_username@remote_ip  Show running jupyter notebook jupyter notebook list  Select column 1 to 4 from data frame using lapply lapply(list, &quot;[&quot;, c(1:4))  &hellip;

